cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new method for generating sequences, which involves training a single encoder and decoder to generate sequences in both left-to-right and right-to-left directions. This involves optimizing the model's parameters, which suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the paper uses neural networks, which could also place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses translation tasks, which could also place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as translation is a common task in computer vision.
